The exchange is that any information you submit to them is theirs, and they're going to do

00:12:05.580 --> 00:12:06.580
whatever they want with it.

00:12:06.580 --> 00:12:12.539
So it's only free in that sense.

00:12:12.539 --> 00:12:15.900
Here is the more screenshot-able table.

00:12:15.900 --> 00:12:18.380
So I did write this package.

00:12:18.380 --> 00:12:23.460
As I was writing it, I was using Anthropics Cloud, which is the default model when you

00:12:23.460 --> 00:12:26.640
call chat-anthropic with Helmer.

00:12:26.640 --> 00:12:31.059
If you just want to get a sense of like, is this something I'm interested in using, put

00:12:31.059 --> 00:12:35.219
$0.50 on an API key and give it a whirl.

00:12:35.219 --> 00:12:39.539
And I think that will give you the best results and maybe show you what's possible there.

00:12:40.260 --> 00:12:46.260
Again, chat, GitHub, you have access to some really good leading models.

00:12:46.260 --> 00:12:54.460
Usually as OpenAI releases new GPT releases, they're available on GitHub within a few days.

